latestPosts.caption:
Tension. Texture. Composition.
An editorial braid story where hair becomes part of the frame-sculpted to flow with movement and line.

From a hairstyling perspective, this look explores weight, control, and form. Each braid is placed with intent to complement the body’s silhouette while staying editorially clean.

Styled with contrast-soft fleece meets structured drape-bringing balance to the boldness of the hair.
Photographed with clean light and negative space to let the textures do the talking.

✨Curious how shoots like this come together from hair to frame?
🚨Limited spots left for our upcoming masterclass— learn how to prep, style, and direct for editorial sessions.
